pe="table" rid="pntd-0000491-t004">Table 4</xref>), where all non-cured categories (missing, not improved/worse) were considered failures, a statistically significant difference was found in cure rates between the two groups at 12 months.</p><table-wrap id="pntd-0000491-t004" position="float"><object-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1371/journal.pntd.0000491.t004</object-id><label>Table 4</label><caption><title>Response of lesions to treatment among subjects treated with imiquimod 5&#x00025; cream plus pentavalent antimony versus placebo cream plus pentavalent antimony, intention-to-treat analysis (missing&#x0200a;=&#x0200a;failures).</title></caption><alternatives><graphic id="pntd-0000491-t004-4" xlink:href="pntd.0000491.t004"/><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><colgroup span="1"><col align="left" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/></colgroup><thead><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Time after the end of therapy, response</td><td colspan="2" align="left" rowspan="1">No. (&#x00025;) of subjects</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">
